  "metadata": {
    "authors": [
      "out-of-line-expression-templates conformance"
    ],
    "description": "esm-spec §9.6.4 rule 3 (RFC out-of-line-expression-templates §9.2). Two match-less templates: `deriv_c` carries a spatial `D` in its body (TARGET-BEARING), so its reference is EAGER — expanded innermost-first in the pre-pass, surfacing the `D`, which the `central` match rule then lowers at load. `scale_c` is target-free, so its reference SURVIVES load and is materialized into the emitted registry. Positive (eager, lowered) + negative (surviving) in one document.",
    "name": "eager_target_bearing"
  },
